A former minister of Aviation, Mr. Femi Fani Kayode has said that Governor Bello Matawalle’s coming into leadership was sent by God to save humanity. Addressing newsmen in Gusau, the Zamfara State capital, Kayode said what happened in the state before the coming of the Matawalle administration was a clear genocide. “It was on record that, before the coming of this administration, the killing in Zamfara State could be rated as genocide, where hundreds of people were being killed in a day”, he added. He described the peace initiative embarked upon by the  Zamfara State government as a welcome development. The former minister however, solicited for collaborative effort to preach against banditry. “Let me stress that, what has been happening in Zamfara needs to be properly publicised and supported by all well meaning Nigerians”, he added. Kayode lauded the RUGA policy initiated by Matawalle administration as great effort to bring peace in the state. “I personally visited  the RUGA project being executed by the present government, it’s a very good project which ought to be supported as means to end banditry”, he added.